 i.e.\nsoftening with increasing luminosity. We find no definitive spectral signatures\nto indicate that these sources contain neutron star primaries, and conclude\nthat they are likely to be stellar-mass black hole XRBs, with black hole masses\nof ~2-23 solar masses if accreting at the Eddington limit (abridged).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 17 Dec 2003 19:29:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
