r base spacetime units. On the basis of such a physical\npicture of spacetime, in a fairly natural way we re-derive a new classical\ndynamical equation which satisfies a more realistic and moderately general\nprinciple of relativity. To further examine this physical picture including of\ngravitation and spacetime, we also reinterpret the gravitational redshifts for\nsolar gravity tests.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 18 Dec 2003 08:39:35 GMT"},{"version":"v10","created":"Sat, 19 Sep 2015 01:12:04 GMT"},{"version":"v11","created":"Tue, 26 Jan 2016 15:16:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 17 Nov 2006 09:20:11 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 23 Nov 2011 01:30:10 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 6 Dec 2011 17:25:47 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sun, 12 Feb 2012 02:33:43 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Fri, 9 Nov 2012 11:01:14 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Tue, 20 Nov 2012 03:15:52 GMT"},{"version":"v8","created":"Mon, 26 Nov 2012 06:59:04 GMT"},{"version":"v9","created":"Thu, 18 Apr 2013 07:59:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-01-27"}
